OL,3,CThree Northern Ireland teaching unions
OL,4,Cvote to accept pay offer
OL,6,FTwo teaching unions in Northern
OL,7,FIreland have voted to accept a pay
OL,8,Foffer from the Department of Education.
OL,10,FThe NASUWT union said 82% of its
OL,11,Fmembers had voted in favour of
OL,12,Faccepting the terms of the 2021 to 24
OL,13,Fpay offer, as part of the process for
OL,14,Fsecuring resolution of their ongoing
OL,15,Fdispute with the Department of
OL,16,FEducation.
OL,18,FThe unions INTO and NEU have also
OL,19,Fbacked the move.
